author: Inside Edition
description: Husband-to-be Steven Goncalves is the brother of Kaylee Goncalves, one of the four roommates murdered by Bryan Kohberger at the University of Idaho. His fiance is Olivia Vitale and she is a journalist who covered the quadruple murder for her true-crime YouTube channel "Chronicles of Olivia." She also interviewed Steven for the Peacock documentary "The Idaho Student Murders." Now the couple has a joint YouTube channel. They spoke with Inside Edition.
title: Kaylee Goncalves' Brother Engaged to Idaho Murder Case Journalist

author: Inside Edition
description: Beloved TV judge Frank Caprio has been laid to rest and countless fans, including past defendants, flocked to say goodbye. At the Rhode Island memorial Thursday, hundreds lined up to pay respects to the beloved jurist, who died August 20 at age 88. Appearing on the TV show "Caught in Providence" while already in his 80s, Caprio touched countless viewers with kindness and compassion that were second to none.
title: Many Pay Their Respects to Beloved TV Judge Frank Caprio

author: Inside Edition
description: Karen Read spoke out about the just announced TV series about her notorious murder trials and she is not happy. She was acquitted in June in the murder of her boyfriend, Boston cop John O'Keefe. Elizabeth Banks is set to play Read in the new drama series for prime TV and Read says the 52-year-old actress is too old. Read and her attorney Alan Jackson say they sold the rights to their story to another Hollywood studio, not the Elizabeth Banks project.
title: Karen Read Voices Disapproval of TV Series About Her Murder Trials

author: Inside Edition
description: It's expected that 17 million people are to take to the skies this Labor Day weekend. The Herzog family of Portland, Oregon, wrapped up their trip to Disneyland and headed home with 4-year-old Sienna and 7-year-old August. They took advantage of Families on the Fly, a new program being introduced at a number of airports. They can go through a dedicated lane for families with kids under the age of 12. Inside Edition also shares some good news for those on a budget this holiday.
title: 'Families on the Fly' Helps These Families Traveling During Holiday

author: Inside Edition
description: FBI agents arrived at the Florida home of 67-year-old Mary Grace Westman, the mother of the Minneapolis Catholic school shooter who killed two children and wounded 18. There was no answer at the home, and it is not known if she was home at the time. However, late Friday, there seemed to be a breakthrough communicating with the shooter's parents. Meanwhile, the families of the two murdered children, 8-year-old Fletcher Merkel and 10-year-old Harper Moyski are speaking out.
title: Families of Children Murdered in Minneapolis School Shooting Speak Out

author: Inside Edition
description:
A day at the spa was anything but relaxing for this suspect. KCNC reports Idaho Springs Police in Colorado were called to the Indian Hot Springs about a credit card fraud alert. 
When officers confronted the suspect, Alec Bogus, 33, they say he took off. Bodycam shows the chase that ensued as he ran through a wooded area in a Speedo-type bathing suit. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Suspect in Speedo Runs From Police Who Caught Up With Him at Colorado Spa

author: Inside Edition
description: A school in Minnesota was thrown for a loop when a pair of ospreys decided to build a nest on one of the towers that light their football field. It presented many problems for Apple Valley High School. The ospreys are protected by law and turning on the lights would harm the animals. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: High School Football Games Re-Scheduled After Ospreys Build Nest on Light Tower
